Reasoning: The paper deals with partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) which are commonly used in robotics applications to model uncertainties in the real world. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with temporal logic specifications and their qualitative analysis, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with control policies and decision-making, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with heuristics and computational complexity, which falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages).
